“Chronal Decay Sculptures: A handheld device utilizing precisely calibrated ultrasonic emissions to induce accelerated, controlled biological decay in plant matter. Users select from a range of 'Chronal Profiles' – ranging from 'Erosion Echo' (simulating glacial retreat, creating fractal patterns in moss and ferns) to 'Crystallization Chorus' (promoting the formation of intricate crystal structures in succulent leaves) to 'Seismic Shift' (mimicking earthquake vibrations, generating chaotic, beautiful distortions in woody stems). The device incorporates a biofeedback loop, monitoring the plant’s response in real-time and adjusting the ultrasonic output for optimal 'Chronal Sculpting.' Includes a built-in spectral analysis display showing the energy being transmitted, and a calming, rhythmic pulsing light that’s purely for aesthetic effect – because, let’s be honest, watching a plant decompose is inherently unsettling! The device also features a ‘Memento’ function, where a 3D scan of the decaying plant is archived, allowing the user to revisit the artistic process.”